body: From the plugin publishing validations: Two of the referenced classes (`com.intellij.util.containers.hash.HashMap` and `com.intellij.util.containers.hash.HashSet`) may be removed in 2020.1 cc @stevemessick, as it looks like they're referenced from the android studio support code.

comment_data.body: Partially fixed in #4390. The change to #doOpenProject needs more investigation.
Steve, do we think this is still an issue for 2020.1?
No, we're good for 2020.1. The remaining change is due to disappear in 2021.3.

It looks like our current product matrix does not yet support 2019.3 EAP (https://github.com/flutter/flutter-intellij/blob/master/product-matrix.json).

@helin24, @stevemessick - can you of you look at adding it to our matrix, to see if we do have issues w/ the next version? Thanks!
I added 2020.3 EAP. The deprecated API only affects Android Studio. I expect the new project wizard re-write will solve that problem long before Android Studio is based on 2020.3.
